Program: Outlook
Title: 30/07/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00vwwc7
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 31 Jul 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world: today, the only woman auto rickshaw driver in the Indian capital Delhi who will be among the senior politicians campaigning to be India's next vice president, the Greek forensic archaeologist who devotes his life to tracking down stolen historical artefacts and the British free diver who held her breath for four minutes to swim more than one hundred metres under the ocean. Show less